 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "MineralWoolAdvisor ⊣ Mineral Wool Plant Operations Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS COORDINATION
 actor for ISIC 2399 (Manufacture of other non-metallic mineral products
 n.e.c.), illustrated concretely with a mineral wool / rock wool
 insulation plant (raw-material melting -> fiberizing -> binder
 application -> curing-oven cure -> cutting/forming line) -- not direct
 forming/curing-line-equipment control authority. Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Eleven concrete governor checks elaborate this
 blueprint's four HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (no direct forming/curing-
 line-equipment control), permanent forming/curing-line-actuate block,
 independent equipment verification/registration before maintenance
 scheduling, independent batch verification/registration before
 shipment coordination, independent shipment-weight recompute against
 the batch's own logged weight, double-schedule guard, product-type
 validation, thermal-conductivity plausibility validation, and density
 plausibility validation. Safety-concern flagging (respirable mineral-
 fibre exposure, forming/curing-line-equipment hazard) ALWAYS escalates
 to a human plant supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is the only op
 eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
